## Code discovery policy
This repo may have one or both pre-built code indexes (CLI-only, no MCP): `.codebase-memory/` (codebase-memory-mcp) and/or `.codegraph/` (codegraph) — unrelated tools, having one does not imply the other.
Project name in the codebase-memory graph, if that index is present: `<PROJECT_NAME>`
For STRUCTURAL questions — where is X defined, who calls X, call chains, change impact / blast radius, architecture overview, dead code, hubs/god-classes, cross-layer violations, which tests cover a change, "which module handles <business term>" — invoke the `code-navigator` skill FIRST; it picks the right underlying tool(s) for the question and for whichever index(es) this repo actually has.
Do not run multi-round Grep/Read exploration for questions the skill answers in one call.
Fall back to native grep/read only for: framework magic (MyBatis XML mapper binding, Vue/React dynamic `import()` route lazy-loading, Eloquent/facades, Blade logic, Django URLconf), class `extends`/inheritance direction, comments/docs, single-file line-level questions, or code changed after the last index sync.
